translations.stoller_miller:
It is more arduous when their reason
clings to my unmanifest nature;
for men constrained by bodies,
the unmanifest way is hard to attain.

translations.gemini:
For knowledge (jñāna) is better than practice (abhyāsa); 
 meditation (dhyāna) is superior to knowledge; 
 From meditation, the abandonment of the fruit of action (karmaphalatyāga); 
 from abandonment, peace (śānti) immediately follows.
